The paper deals with graph drawing algorithms, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of fixed embeddings and the study of beyond-planar graphs suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The optimization of curve complexity and the consideration of optimal layouts suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
